  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nRunning `multiNodeSingleThread.test.ts` with 128 validators per node and there are errors like this:\r\n```\r\n2021-03-30 17:57:28 [NODE 1 VALI 128-255] error: Failed to produce aggregate and proof message=No matching attestations found for attestationData\r\nError: No matching attestations found for attestationData\r\n    at ValidatorApi.getAggregatedAttestation (/Users/tuyennguyen/Projects/workshop/lodestar/packages/lodestar/src/api/impl/validator/validator.ts:123:13)\r\n    at runMicrotasks (<anonymous>)\r\n    at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:93:5)\r\n    at AttestationService.aggregateAttestations (/Users/tuyennguyen/Projects/workshop/lodestar/packages/validator/src/services/attestation.ts:273:19)\r\n    at Timeout._onTimeout (/Users/tuyennguyen/Projects/workshop/lodestar/packages/validator/src/services/attestation.ts:212:13)\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nAt least there should be 1 attestation coming from that same aggregator\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\n\r\n`yarn test:sim:singleThreadMultiNode`\r\n",
